  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Obese patients undergoing bariatric surgery warrant VTE prophylaxis because they are at high
      risk for developing a fatal pulmonary embolism or postthrombotic syndrome. However, a
      consensus does not exist on the most effective prophylactic approach.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Two regimens of prophylaxis are supposed , the 1st one is to give enoxaparin 40mg 2 hours
      before surgery and continued daily for 10 days after, and the 2nd one is to start 12 hours
      before surgery and continued in the same way like the 1st one.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
